<item>
            <title>[WFLY-5235] CDI interceptors are not called when invoking private observer method</title>
                <link>https://issues.jboss.org/browse/WFLY-5235</link>
                <project id="12313721" key="WFLY">WildFly</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The following code runs with an active transaction on WFLY 8.2.0, but failes with an TransactionRequiredException on WFLY 9.0.1:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;@ApplicationScoped&lt;br/&gt;
public class InitCocktailDemoDataService&lt;br/&gt;
{&lt;br/&gt;
  @PersistenceContext&lt;br/&gt;
  private EntityManager entityManager;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  @Transactional&lt;br/&gt;
  private void createDemoData(@Observes @Initialized(ApplicationScoped.class) Object event)&lt;/p&gt;
  {
        this.entityManager.merge(someEntity);
      }

&lt;p&gt;It seems that interceptors aren&apos;t called at all - at least for observers of scope lifecycle events.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
